gitblob.py
==========
Delivers Git-based websites via apache2/mod_python

Author: Armin Pech <github (at) arminpech (dot) de>

Description
===========

Setup with Apache2
==================
* Install mod_python for Apache2 webserver
* Setup a local Git repository on your desktop and create a directory structure
* Create a VHost in your webserver configuration
<VirtualHost *:80>
	# VHost information
	ServerName arminpech.local
	ServerAdmin hostmaster@arminpech.de

	DocumentRoot /dev/null

	# Define logging
	LogLevel warn
	ErrorLog /var/log/apache2/error_log-%{SERVER_NAME}
	CustomLog /var/log/apache2/access_log-%{SERVER_NAME} vhost

	# Secure access to the filesystem
	<Directory />
		Order allow,deny
		Deny from all
	</Directory>

	# Deliver content from git repo by mod_python
	SetHandler mod_python
	PythonOptimize On
	PythonAutoReload Off
	PythonDebug Off
	PythonHandlerModule /usr/local/bin/gitblog.py.git/gitblog.py
	PythonOption gitblog.wwwroot /var/git/arminpech.de.git/
	PythonOption gitblog.report_errors True

	# Compress output by filter
	SetOutputFilter DEFLATE
</VirtualHost>
